    , notes := "The completeness side now exposes the initial signed search state induced by a frontier, together with a native staged bridge from that frontier into the local saturation layer, an agenda of branching obligations detected so far, and explicit local branch resolution operations. The branch agenda is tied to a preserved visibility invariant, every pending target and every admissible resolution is justified by a signed premise already present in the current Hintikka staging set, the old head-based resolution interface is factored through a more canonical focused-obligation layer, honest search moves are packaged as either triggered saturation steps or focused resolutions, and these now generate a finite reachability relation whose runs preserve both agenda visibility and the original signed frontier formulas. A rooted `SearchRun` layer packages those finite runs over one fixed initial frontier, an explicit `SearchDerivation` layer records honest finite search histories inductively, the stricter `HeadSearchDerivation` sublayer removes arbitrary focus choice by insisting that branch resolution always consumes the current agenda head, the `ProductiveTriggeredLocalStep` / `ProductiveHeadSearchDerivation` layer excludes vacuous repeated saturation by requiring each saturation step to contribute at least one genuinely new signed formula, the `HeadPrioritySearchDerivation` layer sharpens the policy further by allowing productive saturation only while the agenda is empty, the terminal/completion layer connects local search quiescence to the pre-existing `HintikkaSet.LocallySaturated` notion, and `CountermodelCandidate` now packages that terminal head-priority completion as the current world-free countermodel-facing object together with the derived branch-closure certificate needed to extract supported local resolving steps for visible branch targets. The bridge layer still exposes the stronger consistency-based upgrades, but the semilocal model interface itself has now been weakened to the paper-facing `LocalHintikkaCertificate`, and the closed-hull route can therefore pass from search data to `LocalAgreementWitness`, `LocalCountermodel`, and `SoundLocalCountermodel` using non-contradiction alone once the semantic truth assignments are provided. This is a more faithful search-to-countermodel construction interface, but it still stops short of proving non-contradiction or the full semantic model from the search side itself, and no world-indexed forcing or final completeness theorem is claimed yet." }
